    "main_contenido_marco_B67PbF": {
      "type": "main-contenido-marco",
      "custom_css": [],
      "settings": {
        "invertir_orden": false,
        "habilitar_imagen_fondo": false,
        "color_fondo": "#fff9f1",
        "titulo": "From Local Farms",
        "clase_titulo": "Titulo-Nickson-six-h1",
        "color_titulo": "#9a7a4b",
        "subtitulo": "to Local Classrooms",
        "clase_subtitulo": "Titulo-Nickson-four-h1-portada",
        "color_subtitulo": "#002554",
        "texto": "<p>We’re helping to expand the local food system’s capacity to deliver local, organic food to K12 students with a collaborative solution that meets mutual needs of small producers and school districts.<\/p>",
        "color_texto": "#002554",
        "ocultar_botones": true,
        "mostrar_dos_botones": false,
        "texto_boton_1": "Learn More  →",
        "enlace_boton_1": "",
        "color_boton_1": "#c9a76d",
        "color_texto_boton_1": "#002554",
        "boton_1_transparente": false,
        "texto_boton_2": "K12 Portal →",
        "enlace_boton_2": "",
        "color_boton_2": "#002554",
        "color_texto_boton_2": "#002554",
        "boton_2_transparente": true,
        "imagen_fondo_contenedor": "shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Illustration_fb8b4eec-246a-4858-82ed-19f18c7641cb.png",
        "habilitar_video_fondo": false,
        "url_video_fondo": ""
      }
    },
    "main_contenedor_titular_cuerpo_unicolumna_nW4mqP": {
      "type": "main-contenedor-titular-cuerpo-unicolumna",
      "settings": {
        "background_color": "#d6e8ff",
        "habilitar_imagen_fondo": false,
        "padding_top": 20,
        "padding_bottom": 20,
        "titulo": "Stronger Together",
        "clase_titulo": "Titulo-Nickson-four-h1",
        "color_titulo": "#002554",
        "ocultar_subtito": false,
        "subtitulo": "",
        "clase_subtitulo": "Titulo-Nickson-six-h2",
        "color_subtitulo": "#c9a76d",
        "texto": "<p>It takes a village to feed and raise children, so let’s join K12 food-service professionals, farmers and food hubs across the state to collaborate and share knowledge and resources.<\/p>",
        "color_texto": "#666666",
        "ocultar_botones": true,
        "mostrar_dos_botones": false,
        "texto_boton_1": "Explore our impact  →",
        "enlace_boton_1": "",
        "color_boton_1": "#002554",
        "color_texto_boton_1": "#ffffff",
        "boton_1_transparente": false,
        "texto_boton_2": "Contact",
        "enlace_boton_2": "",
        "color_boton_2": "#002554",
        "color_texto_boton_2": "#002554",
        "boton_2_transparente": true
      }
    },
    "main_contenedor_multicolumnas_bloques_MKrFYQ": {
      "type": "main-contenedor-multicolumnas-bloques",
      "blocks": {
        "bloque_multicolumna_d6JJYF": {
          "type": "bloque_multicolumna",
          "settings": {
            "top_image": "shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Icono-01.png",
            "clase_imagen": "Mediano-imagen-multicolumna",
            "block_background_color": "#f5f5f5",
            "transparent_background": true,
            "title": "School district demand",
            "clase_subtitulo": "Titulo-Nickson-four-h3",
            "title_color": "#002554",
            "text": "<p>California is the first state to mandate schools provide a nutritiously adequate breakfast and lunch to every student regardless of income,  increasing demand from 3,075,721 students qualifying for free lunch in the 2022-2023 school year* to 5,852,544 students enrolled in California’s 10,010 schools across 1,018 districts. <br\/>*California Department of Education<br\/><\/p>",
            "text_color": "#333333"
          }
        },
        "bloque_multicolumna_rpCKUF": {
          "type": "bloque_multicolumna",
          "settings": {
            "top_image": "shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Icono-02.png",
            "clase_imagen": "Mediano-imagen-multicolumna",
            "block_background_color": "#f5f5f5",
            "transparent_background": true,
            "title": "local farm supply",
            "clase_subtitulo": "Titulo-Nickson-four-h3",
            "title_color": "#002554",
            "text": "<p>Small independent producers face common barriers in supplying farm to school ingredients that require specialized packaging, distribution, and marketing. 94% percent of rural North Coast dairy farmers have less than 500 cows compared to the rest of the state where 53% of farms have more than 500 cows. Lower volumes make it critical to receive the highest value for the milk.<br\/>*USDA Census of Agriculture<br\/><\/p>",
            "text_color": "#333333"
          }
        },
        "bloque_multicolumna_UVp8dr": {
          "type": "bloque_multicolumna",
          "settings": {
            "top_image": "shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Icono-03.png",
            "clase_imagen": "Mediano-imagen-multicolumna",
            "block_background_color": "#f5f5f5",
            "transparent_background": true,
            "title": "Farm to School\u2028Capacity",
            "clase_subtitulo": "Titulo-Nickson-four-h3",
            "title_color": "#002554",
            "text": "<p>Rumiano aggregates, processes, and markets organic dairy products made from milk supplied by 20 local family farms. We also partner with 21 California school districts serving a collective 220,000 students, to address unique challenges in expanding the local food systems capacity and model Farm-to-School sales of locally-produced organic dairy products across California. <\/p>",
            "text_color": "#333333"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "bloque_multicolumna_d6JJYF",
        "bloque_multicolumna_rpCKUF",
        "bloque_multicolumna_UVp8dr"
      ],
